Legal Calculus 4.5 — Enhanced Modules — Module 17
📘 Legal Calculus — Module 17

Declarations & 28 U.S.C. § 1746

⚖️ Core Message

Facts under penalty of perjury carry weight and travel across forums.
📖 Lesson Content

1. Use unsworn declarations (28 U.S.C. § 1746) when notarization is impractical.
2. Personal knowledge only; no legal argument inside the declaration.
3. Label exhibits clearly and reference by page.
4. Close with the exact perjury language and a signature/date line.
📝 Assignment

Draft a one‑page unsworn declaration with three numbered facts and two exhibit cites.
✅ Model Response

DECLARATION OF CHARLES MAYRON

 

1. I have personal knowledge of the facts stated herein.

2. On July 31, 2025, USPS delivered my motion to the Clerk (Ex. A at 1).

3. The Clerk docketed the motion on Aug. 2, 2025 (Dkt 18).

 

I declare under penalty of perjury that the foregoing is true and correct.

Executed on August 18, 2025.         /s/ Charles Mayron

 

💡 Reflection Summary

Say it under penalty of perjury — and cite exhibits.
🎨 Visual Concept

A signature line over the words 'under penalty of perjury'.
